      <section eId="sec_2215">
        <num>2215</num>
        <heading>Relief demanded by other than moving party</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2215__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of rule 2214, a party may serve upon the moving party a\nnotice of cross-motion demanding relief, with or without supporting\npapers; provided, however, that:\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2215__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>if such notice and any supporting papers are served by mailing, as\nprovided in paragraph two of subdivision</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2215__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of rule 2103, they shall be\nserved three days earlier than as prescribed in this rule; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2215__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>if served by overnight delivery, as provided in paragraph six of\nsubdivision</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2215__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of rule 2103, they shall be served one day earlier than\nas prescribed in this rule. Relief in the alternative or of several\ndifferent types may be demanded; relief need not be responsive to that\ndemanded by the moving party.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
